---
description: Standard steps that every implementation plan must include.
globs: "**/*.plan.md"
alwaysApply: true
---

Every implementation plan must include these steps in this order. Add them as both plan sections and frontmatter todos.

### Beginning of every plan

- **Branch setup**: Create fresh feature branches from the repository's default branch in every submodule that will be changed. Branch naming convention: `username/TICKET-ID-short-description` (e.g., `alice/ENG-1234-add-retry-logic`).

### End of every plan (after all implementation steps)

- **CI lint and test**: Run the `ci-lint-test` skill for each changed submodule. Fix failures and re-run until clean.
- **Pre-MR checklist**: Run the `pre-mr-checklist` skill on each changed submodule. Fix all blockers.
- **Commit and create MRs**: Commit, push, and create GitLab MRs for each changed submodule. Title must include the ticket ID (`TICKET-ID: Short description`). Assign self, add reviewer. MR descriptions must follow the merge-requests rule.
